comments: Ayton (PHX) cleanly blocks Siakam (TOR) during his driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Anunoby (TOR) and absorbs the contact.
Lowry (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Booker (PHX).

Ayton (PHX) inadvertently makes contact to Anunoby's (TOR) head during rebounding.   Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Lowry (TOR) makes contact to Paul's (PHX) body on the start of his drive and affects his SQBR.
Paul (PHX) places his arms against VanVleet (TOR) and marginal contact occurs as he releases.
VanVleet (TOR) makes contact to Paul's (PHX) arm during the side-to-side motion of his rip-through.
VanVleet (TOR) maintains a collapsed arm when contact occurs with Crowder (PHX) and he does not dislodge him from his position as he changes directions.
Anunoby (TOR) makes marginal contact to Booker's (PHX) arm during the drive and does not affect his control of the ball.
Paul (PHX) loses his balance upon receiving the pass and goes to the floor.  Paul does not commit a traveling violation and PHX signals for a timeout before any possible held ball.
Trent Jr. (TOR) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
